###  https://blue-room-innovation.github.io/bri-ontology/codelists/v0.1/unlocode.ttl#UNLocodeScheme
<https://blue-room-innovation.github.io/bri-ontology/codelists/v0.1/unlocode.ttl#UNLocodeScheme> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                                                          <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#ConceptScheme> ;
                                                                                                 dcterms:source <https://unece.org/trade/cefact/unlocode-code-list-country-and-territory> ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A standardized code that uniquely identifies geographical locations used in international trade and transport, as defined by UNECE."@en ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note> "Referenced by properties such as :arrivalPort, :nextPlannedDeliveryPort, :lastWasteDeliveryPort, and :nextCollectionPort in the Digital MARPOL Waste Passport ontology. These properties should use valid UN/LOCODE values to identify ports or geographical locations."@en ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "UN/LOCODE"@en ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "This scheme references the official UN/LOCODE dataset published by UNECE. Implementations should use codes directly from that source (e.g., ESPMI for Palma de Mallorca, ESBCN for Barcelona)."@en .


